OL,5,FTHE 1NT OPENING BID by Andrew Kambites 
OL,7,          CThe Mini No-Trump            
OL,8, Why do you usually open with 12 points 
OL,9, and pass with 11? The answer is that if
OL,10, both players pass with a good 12-count 
OL,11, a game contract may be missed. If both 
OL,12, pass with 11 a part-score may be lost, 
OL,13, but that is less damaging. Bidding     
OL,14, theory stresses bidding your games!    
OL,16,GSo can you see any       CSFK J 6      
OL,17, case for opening the     CHFA 6 2      
OL,18, bidding withF1NTGif      CDFJ 10 8     
OL,19, you have this hand?      CCFQ 9 8 2    
